<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98220486923783>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>A Guide to Focus Items</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Feb 14th 9:41 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=844><span id= >Galuvyen</span></a><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.63]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's some information regarding the focus items that result from the quests in The Temple of Solusek Ro.<br><br>GENERAL INFO:<br>There are four focus items, one for each element-<br>Broom of Trilon - Air<br>Torch of Alna&nbsp;&nbsp; - Fire<br>Shovel of Ponz  - Earth<br>Stein of Ulisa  - Water<br><br>All of the items are no drop, magic, lore weapons.<br>They all share 6 damage, 23 delay (or 28, can't remember), one hand blunt skill, and +2 intelligence.  They also carry the following stats:<br>Broom - +3 agi<br>Torch - +5 sv fire<br>Stein - +5 sv cold<br>Shovel- +3 str<br><br>The main use of the focus items is to increase the hit points and stats of your pet.  Hit points increase in the following manner:<br>Earth with Shovel - +10-20% roughly<br>Water with Stein  - Same HP as normal earth pet<br>Air with Broom    - Same HP as normal water pet<br>Fire with Torch   - Same HP as normal air pet<br>The focus items apparently increase stats such as strength and dexterity for the pet, but this is harder to determine.  Now for help with the quests themselves....<br><br>DIFFICULTY<br><br>All of these quests can be done at a very low level with some luck and some money. All of the components are tradeable and most are relatively cheap.  The quest can be done safely at level 34, you should then be able to kill what you need for the rarer parts.<br><br>BROOM OF TRILON<br><br>The Broom of Trilon quest consists of 3 parts that are easily bought at vendors and "a broom" from Najena or The Lost Temple of Cazic-Thule.<br>a.) Griffon/in feathers- these can be looted from griffons (100% sure) griffennes (100% sure) and griffawns (90% sure).  I personally found mine on a barbarian vendor in East Karana, someone had sold them.<br>b.) Cyclops Toes - Cyclopes should be soloable at 34 with a little trouble.  These toes can also be found on vendors in cyclops-populated areas.<br>c.) Star Ruby - bought at a gem shop<br>d.) A Broom - This is the hardest part of the quest.  They are rare drops off magicians in Najena and alligators in Cazic-Thule.  At 35, I could get to a point in Najena with magicians and everything was very green to me.  Alligators can be as strong as cyclopes/hill giants or as low as level 20, it's random.  The broom is nodrop and can be bought from other players occaisionally.<br><br>SHOVEL OF PONZ<br>a.) Gargoyle Eyes - Easily found on gargoyles in Ocean of Tears or Mistmoore castle.  I easily defeated a level 18 or so gargoyle in OOT and looted 2 eyes, and that was part of the quest for my mage friend and me :)  Just be careful because the gargoyles spawn on spectre island.<br>b.) Hill Giant toes - Found on Hill Giants and on vendors in hill giant populated areas occaisionally.  I bought some on AC island from the magician spell merchant.  She had a stock of Fire, Frost (really Ice), and Hill giant toes.  This might have been a fluke but I have heard that she has them all the time.<br>c.) Ruby - bought at gem merchants<br>d.) A Shovel - see A Broom above...<br><br>TORCH OF ALNA<br>a.) Fire Drake scales - a somewhat rare drop from the level 15-20ish fire drakes in Lavastorm.  I found one in 3 or 4 kills.<br>b.) Fire Giant toes - Perhaps the hardest toes to loot as fire giants are found deep in Nagafen's Lair (sol b).  These also drop off of Gornit in OOT and I found a supply of them at the magician merchant on AC isle.<br>c.) Fire Emerald - found in gem shops<br>d.) A Torch - See A Broom and A Shovel above...<br><br>STEIN OF ULISSA<br>a.) Mermaid Scales - The easiest of the generic monster quest parts.  The level 12 sirens on the rocky islands near the Butcherblock zone in OOT drop these quite frequently.<br>b.) Frost Giant Toes - Although the quest says FROST giant toes, these are actually the toes from ICE giants.  <br>DO NOT USE TOES FROM FROST GIANTS ON VELIOUS!<br>Ice giants in Everfrost/Permafrost drop these, as well as Gornit in OOT.  I again found them at the magician merchant on AC Isle.<br>c.) Sapphire - bought at a gem merchant<br>d.) A Stein - see A Torch, A Shovel, A Broom above..<br><br>Well that is ALL I know about getting these items, they truly are great additions to the mage's equipment.<br><br>Note: It would be nice to have more information about the 3 giant toes on the merchant on AC Island.  Can anyone confirm or deny their permanence in the shop inventory?<br><br>Denevian, Level FORTY :) I mean &gt;:(<br></p>&nbsp;<br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
