	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>TOES:<br>Depending on your level, you can hunt Gornet, a named hill giant in the Ocean of Tears.&nbsp;&nbsp;He drops all 4 types of giant toes.  A 34 mage and 29ish druid can do this pretty easily.  At 39, you should be able to solo this guy.  If you are too young yet, you might also check all the vendors around there for the toes.  There is a dwarf and a woodelf vendor on sister island that people commonly sell thier hunting spoils at.<br><br>If you have no luck with oot, you can check vendors at Rathe Mountains for cyclopse and hill giant toes, Lavastorm for fire giant toes, and Everfrost for ice giant toes.<br><br>MAJOR COMPONENT:<br>You will most likely have to hunt up your stein, shovel, broom, and torch.  All but the torch can be gotten from gators in Cazic Thule.  You will probably want a partner/group if you are lower than 34, and even then it is pretty risky.  The torch is easily achieved by killing mages in Najena.<br><br>MINOR COMPONENT:<br>It is not likely you will be able to buy any of these.  You can get your griffon feather off all the different griffs (yes, griffawns, griffenes, griffins, griffons).  The best place for this is North Karana near the tower guards.  You might even be lucky to find one on one of the gypsie vendors in the zone.  Gargoyle eyes are from gargoyles in Ocean of Tears or Mistmoore.  The oot ones are easier to get to at lower levels due to the higher level spawns around at Mistmoore.  Not likely to find these on vendors.  Mermaid scales again are in oot.  You will not likely find them on vendors.  Fire drake scales drop off of roaming drakes in lavastorm.<br><br>GEMS:<br>Either get charasima gear or start an enchanter mule with all the bonus points towards cha.  This will get your gems at lower prices, saving you big time pp's.  I am not sure of all the cities that they can be bought in, but I do know that they are in Qeynos, Freeport, and Felwithe.<br><br>Good luck fellow mages!</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
