	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>390 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.58]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I never saw giant toes when I went to the merchant on AC isle.*shrug*. Also, the earth pet has the same HP with the focus item, just a lot more agility. Since the earth pet's natural agility is about 70, it normally gets hit a LOT more than usual and takes a lot of damage per hit. This is becuase if your agility is below 75 your chances of getting hit increase a LOT and your AC also takes a plunge. The focus item makes it so that your earth pet now has above 75 agility, which makes a HUGE difference.<br><br>The pets DID seem to hit a bit harder with the focus items, so the focus items probably grant a bonus to strength and/or atk.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
